# Memory Bounty — Project Context

## What This Project Is

A **codebase memory ingestion pipeline** (write side only). One TypeScript file goes in; structured semantic memory comes out, stored in Cloudflare Vectorize + D1. Future agents will query this memory — that retrieval side is out of scope here.

**Pipeline:** `file` → Tree-sitter chunks → Cursor SDK descriptions → Workers AI embeddings → Vectorize + D1

## Implementation Status

**Phase 1 (Base) is COMPLETE.** The end-to-end pipeline works: chunk → describe → embed → store.

Read `docs/STATUS.md` immediately for:
- Exactly what has been built and what hasn't
- Known bugs and quirks
- Prioritized next steps for Phase 2

## Key Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/types.ts` | `Chunk` interface shared across CLI and Worker |
| `src/chunker.ts` | Tree-sitter TypeScript AST → `Chunk[]` |
| `src/ingest.ts` | CLI: chunk → describe via `@cursor/sdk` → POST to Worker |
| `worker/index.ts` | Cloudflare Worker: embed (`bge-small-en-v1.5`) → Vectorize + D1 |
| `worker/wrangler.toml` | Worker config (AI, Vectorize `memory-bounty-index`, D1 `memory-bounty-db`) |
| `migrations/001_init.sql` | D1 schema |
| `docs/STATUS.md` | **Living status doc — always check this first** |

## Critical Architectural Note

The `implementation_plan.md` says descriptions are generated by the Worker (Workers AI). **This is wrong.** Descriptions are generated **on the CLI side** via `@cursor/sdk` `Agent.prompt` (model: `composer-2`) in `src/ingest.ts`. The Worker only embeds and stores.

